						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: Śaka 1575. <hi rend="italic">Kollam</hi> 829, <hi rend="italic">Viśaiya, Tai</hi> 23, Friday, 13, <hi rend="italic">Puṇar pūśam</hi> = 1653 A.D. Other details are irregular.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that Viśvaṉātha Nāyakkar and Tirumalai Nāyakkar had got the procession of the god, conducted, for the merit of a certain Vaḍamalai Pappu-piḷḷai. It is also stated that this was the charity of Bhūtaṉāthaṉ.</p>						

